review_blob: Very disappointing from a brewery that rarely disappoints. This beer just does nothing for me. I do brew beer and I know what it is like to make a beer that fails, but when I do, I dont let my friends taste it, let alone put it on the market. Im sorry lett hand, but this beer is really really bad in my opinion, That said, I do love every other beer I have ever had from you but this one just.....no
This is what a tripel should taste like in my opinion. Nice and smooth with not too much alcohol or citrus. Nicely balanced, good color with great head
best beer ever. A perfect score on tap but only a humble 4.7 bottled. I love this beer

I would like to thank this beer for showing me just how important the presense of wheat and barley is to make a decent beer. This beer does have potential for something but They should stop classifying it as an Abby Tripel and start selling it as an organic beer to get college girls drunk cause it taistes like a wine cooler. I had to dump this one out and nothing pains me more than dumping out a beer!

I got this beer at world market of all places for about $7. Good appearance, a nice creamy body and smooth lasting head.  A nice spicy aroma of banana and citrus, good Tripel aroma. Good initial flavor with a nice balance of alcohol.  The finish is a little bitter but an excellent beer.

Drink Turtle Piano!

I would like to say that this is my favorite beer right now. It is so refreshing in the summertime. It is a nice cloudy gold on the eye and a beautiful fruity smell with strong scents of banana and hints of clove and apple. It tastes much like the smell with a mild finish that gives it a refreshing summer feel that leaves you wanting more. love this beer
A very good beer! Great flavors...a lot of them. I love it when a US brewery gets it right. A truely nice ale
